- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is likely because the paper deals with the concept of computability and degrees of discontinuity, which are closely related to logic and formal systems. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also likely because the paper discusses the computational power of different types of computation and their relationship to the Analytical Hierarchy. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category because the paper deals with the concept of representation and revising computation, which are relevant to programming language design and implementation. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is possible because the paper may involve the analysis of algorithms for computing discontinuous functions. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is possible because the paper may involve the analysis of information content and complexity in the representation and computation of discontinuous functions.
